Public Works and Infrastructure Minister Patricia De Lille has confirmed the suspension of Director-General Advocate Sam Vukela. JOHANNESBURG - The Minister of Public Works and Infrastructure, Patricia De Lille confirmed on Wednesday that the Director-General of the Department of Public Works and Infrastructure (DPWI), Advocate Sam Vukela was placed on precautionary suspension. READ: DG guilty of negligence in R500m lease scandal The suspension is effective as of Wednesday 29 July - pending the finalisation of the disciplinary processes instituted against the DG. Vukela has been implicated in massive overspending on state funerals and an irregular hiring spree. In a statement, De Lille confirmed that the move comes after reports from two investigations into the matter.